		"description": "<p>Also at 20th level, as an action, you gain the ability to transform yourself into a terrifying being of animate lava. The form lasts for 1 minute. While in this lava form you gain the following benefits:</p><ul><li><p>If you would take fire damage from a source you did not create, you instead regain that many hit points. You may only regain up to 10 hit points this way per turn, with any excess being lost.</p></li><li><p>You grow to large size. Your melee attacks reach an additional 5 feet further than normal, and your unarmed strikes and melee weapon attacks deal an additional 3d6 points of fire damage. A creature hitting you with a melee weapon attack must make a Dexterity saving throw against your maneuver DC or be splashed with lava for 2d6 fire damage.&nbsp;</p></li><li><p>You gain resistance to nonmagical bludgeoning, piercing, and slashing damage.</p></li><li><p>You gain advantage on Intimidate checks.</p></li><li><p>You gain a lava splash attack that acts as a ranged weapon attack dealing 4d6 fire damage with a range of 30/60 feet.</p></li><li><p>Creatures immune to fire are treated as resistant to fire for the purpose of your attacks.</p></li></ul><p style=\"text-align: start\">Once you have used this ability, you canâ€™t do so again until you finish a long rest.</p>",
